Tubatse Carwash and Chisanyama finally opened its doors during a grand opening in Burgersfort. The business officially opened on Saturday June 25. Specials were galore for those who washed
their cars, as well as the ones who ordered their meals. Tubatse Carwash and Chisanyama provides excellent service at affordable prices. The prices for the car wash are affordable, it costs R100 to clean a bigger car, while you can wash a
smaller car for just R70. There are extra charges on for clients who want to wash full house. Trucks can be washed for as little as R400, mini buses cost R200, and to wash a taxi costs R120. The chisanyama offers delicious meals. This includes dishes with mopani worms, mala le maotwana,
chicken and beef. A full plate is between R70 and R65 while half plates are between R50 and R45. According to the management, they aim to grow the businesses all over the country and also outside South
African borders. “Tubatse Carwash aims to grow its business, not only in the Tubatse region, but across the continent. “We aim to be the example of a small start-up which can grow into a franchise. We also pick up cars and
deliver,” said management. They also thanked each and every client who supported them during the opening; they also urged clients to
visit them at any time between 08:00 and 17:00. Tubatse Carwash and Chisanyama is situated at Old Volkswagen, Aloe Ridge West. The business can be
contacted on 076 691 8211/ 074 184 0449. 